This paper involves the study of evacuation strategies in a geometric setting, which suggests that it belongs to the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of optimization techniques and lower bounds also suggests that it could belong to the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). The problem of evacuating a room in the presence of obstacles and time constraints can also be seen as a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of game-theoretic concepts to analyze the problem could also place it in the category of game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the presence of multiple agents and the need for coordination suggests that it could belong to the category of control systems (cs.SY).
